node.text:
It’s night ✌️of rhythmic competition in Tokyo!

Before they hit the floor at 9 ET tonight, take an inside look as to what makes the 🇺🇸 rhythmic group such a dynamic unit!

node.text:
Part II of the Rhythmic 101 series is here!

Former National Team member Jazzy Kerber (@jazinka) breaks down Evita Griskenas’ ball routine ahead of her individual performance in Tokyo! 

Check out the video so you know what to watch for when the competition gets underway at 9:20 ET tonight! 

Missed Jazzy’s first breakdown?

Watch the previous video on IGTV of Team USA’s other individual rhythmic gymnast set for the 🌎 stage, Laura Zeng!

node.text:
Throwing it back to July 4 when Emily Davis and Aubrey Rosilier took home 🥈 in women’s pair at the Acrobatic Gymnastics World Championships! 🙌

Enjoy their dynamic routine from the competition in Geneva, Switzerland! Can’t wait to see you both in action again soon! 🇺🇸

node.text:
As we celebrate Human Rights Day and reflect upon the significance of empowerment and advocacy, we are proud to introduce the USA Gymnastics Athlete Bill of Rights. The bill was created collaboratively with USAG's Athletes' Council as a shared community commitment to athlete wellness.⠀
⠀
All athletes have the right to:⠀
⠀
▶️ Participate in gymnastics⠀
▶️ Train and compete safely⠀
▶️ Have their personal health and wellness prioritized⠀
▶️ Be treated with dignity and respect⠀
▶️ Receive proper instruction⠀
▶️ Provide input on matters that directly affect them⠀
▶️ Voice opinions on issues that affect the gymnastics community⠀
▶️ Expect integrity and transparency⠀
⠀
We've also updated our protest policy for National Team members to help athletes feel more supported when using their public platforms. Swipe up on our story to learn more and access the full Athlete Bill of Rights.

node.title: Introducing our new Athlete Bill of Rights ⬇️

node.text:
It’s night ✌️of rhythmic competition in Tokyo!

Before they hit the floor at 9 ET tonight, take an inside look as to what makes the 🇺🇸 rhythmic group such a dynamic unit!

node.text:
Evita Griskenas placed 12th, while Laura Zeng finished 13th at the Individual Qualification - just missing out on the Final! 

We are so proud of the gymnasts who represented the country on the biggest stage today! 

Forever Olympians ❤️

📸 @johnkcheng

node.text:
Rhythmic gymnastics competition is officially underway in Tokyo! 

We’re at the halfway point of the Individual Qualification and Evita Griskenas sits in 13th place out of 26 gymnasts, while Laura Zeng has posted the 17th-highest mark!

Tune into Rotations 3-4 at 1:50 AM ET later tonight to cheer on Team USA, as the gymnasts with the top-10 scores will advance to the Final! 👏 🇺🇸

📸 @johnkcheng
